		<div class="lia-message-body lia-component-body" id="messagebodydisplay_0_3" class="lia-message-body">
	
		<div class="lia-message-body-content">
			
                
                    <P>After a few seconds, the door swung open. An irritated looking fifteen year old stood in the door, headphones around his neck, a mess of curly brown hair on his head. His irritated look left his face.</P><P>“Well, hello, there. Who might you be?” Max Darkflame said, stuffing the audio device into pocket.</P><P>“Max,” Vanda said. “It’s me. Your sister.”</P><P>Max’s eyes widened. He let go of the door.</P><P>Suddenly, Thomas Darkflame appeared at the door next to Max. “Max, what’s taking…”</P><P>He stopped when he saw Vanda. Recognition flashed in his eyes as he saw his daughter for the first time in five years.</P><P>Tears started flowing from Vanda’s eyes, mingling with the rain on her face. “Daddy, I am so, so sorry,” she began, her voice breaking.</P><P>Her father cut with off, pulling her into a tight hug.</P><P>Vanda sniffed, still crying. “But-“</P><P>“Welcome back, my little girl,” Thomas whispered, his eyes closed as he hugged his daughter.</P><P>A contented smile appeared on Vanda’s face.</P><P>&nbsp;</P>
                
            
			
